A quick and dirty install guide:

1.) Unpack the files and make sure they're readable by your web server. (apache, www-data, etc.)

2.) Create an MySQL database and user.
   CREATE DATABASE ________;
   GRANT ALL ON _______.* TO 'username'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED BY 'supercoolpassword';
   FLUSH PRIVILEGES;

3.) Navigate to the install page.  e.g. http://www.example.com/adventure/install.php

4.) Enter your details the DB info from above and submit.

5.) Create an .htaccess and .htpasswd file to protect your edit and admin pages.

6.) Go to the admin page and cusomize your site.

Best of luck!
